quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  71,21,"Noah said, “O my Lord, they did not follow me, but they follow the people whose wealth and children give them no increase, but only loss"
  71,22,“And they have devised a great plot
  71,23,"“And they said, ‘Do not abandon your gods. Abandon neither Wadd nor Suwa, neither Yaguth nor Ya’uq, nor Nasr"
  71,24,"“They have already misled many, and grant no increase to the wrong-doers, except in misguidance.”"
  71,25,"So because of their sins they were drowned, and were made to enter the fire, and they found, in lieu of God, none to help them"
  71,26,"And Noah said, “O my Lord, do not leave from the unbelievers, a single one on earth"
  71,27,"“For if You do leave them, they will only mislead Your devotees, and they will breed none but wicked ungrateful ones"
  71,28,"“O my Lord, forgive me, my parents, and all who enter my house with belief, and all believing men and believing women, and to the wrongdoers, grant no increase except in perdition.”"